1
00:00:18,435 --> 00:00:21,354
ALL CHARACTERS, ORGANIZATIONS
AND EVENTS IN THIS DRAMA ARE FICTITIOUS

2
00:01:06,483 --> 00:01:07,317
Paik Seung-yoo.

3
00:01:08,943 --> 00:01:09,944
Paik Seung-yoo.

4
00:01:10,570 --> 00:01:11,529
Paik Seung-yoo!

5
00:01:24,584 --> 00:01:25,835
I found you.

6
00:01:36,137 --> 00:01:37,222
Eco bag?

7
00:01:37,305 --> 00:01:38,932
Yes, we got our bags mixed up.

8
00:01:39,516 --> 00:01:41,267
So you go to Asung High?

9
00:01:43,269 --> 00:01:44,604
Let me reintroduce myself.

10
00:01:49,526 --> 00:01:52,779
I teach math at Asung High School.
My name is Ji Yoon-su.

11
00:01:54,656 --> 00:01:55,740
And you're…

12
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:58,409
Paik Seung-yoo?

13
00:02:23,893 --> 00:02:25,645
Do you like math?

14
00:02:27,397 --> 00:02:28,231
No.

15
00:02:36,614 --> 00:02:38,408
This is your answer sheet, right?

16
00:02:40,118 --> 00:02:40,952
No, it's not mine.

17
00:02:43,538 --> 00:02:46,249
This vector sign
is what they use in universities.

18
00:02:48,668 --> 00:02:51,087
Do you expect me to
believe that you don't like math?

19
00:02:54,632 --> 00:02:56,259
You're in big trouble

20
00:02:57,051 --> 00:02:58,469
for lying to me.

21
00:02:59,137 --> 00:03:00,680
You shouldn't lie to your teacher.

22
00:03:03,224 --> 00:03:04,559
I'll give you detention.

23
00:03:05,351 --> 00:03:07,604
Come to this classroom
by 7:30 a.m. on Monday.

24
00:03:07,687 --> 00:03:10,023
-And bring your camera.
-Why do you need my camera?

25
00:03:10,690 --> 00:03:12,108
It's part of your detention.

26
00:03:12,775 --> 00:03:14,068
I'll see you on Monday then.

27
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:22,619
If you're a no-show, I'll dock your grade.

28
00:03:29,918 --> 00:03:30,919
DAD

29
00:03:31,753 --> 00:03:33,880
Don't be late for your 6 p.m. appointment.

30
00:03:56,152 --> 00:03:58,571
It's a tricky math problem.

31
00:03:58,655 --> 00:04:01,241
The author of the problem
wanted it to be too hard to solve.

32
00:04:01,824 --> 00:04:04,619
The teacher told the class that
she wouldn't give out

33
00:04:04,702 --> 00:04:07,330
CSAT prep math problems
to the math club members.

34
00:04:07,413 --> 00:04:09,332
Why did she make them solve this?
It doesn't even help.

35
00:04:09,415 --> 00:04:13,378
I think the teacher, Ms. Ji, is focused
on winning the Math Olympiad.

36
00:04:13,962 --> 00:04:18,925
The 3rd and 6th problems in the Olympiad
are the most difficult of them all.

37
00:04:19,008 --> 00:04:22,095
You can't solve them
by using conventional methods.

38
00:04:22,178 --> 00:04:24,931
I heard that Ye-lin got the answer right.

39
00:04:25,515 --> 00:04:29,269
Gyu-young tells me
that Ye-lin didn't solve it.

40
00:04:29,352 --> 00:04:30,353
Didn't she?

41
00:04:31,980 --> 00:04:33,856
-Then who did?
-Nobody knows.

42
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:36,442
If nobody knows,
then why even bring it up?

43
00:04:36,526 --> 00:04:40,947
You know Gyu-young gets
so competitive around Ye-lin.

44
00:04:41,030 --> 00:04:42,282
Oh, it's warm in here.

45
00:04:42,365 --> 00:04:44,409
-Gosh.
-The weather is so good today.

46
00:04:44,492 --> 00:04:46,452
Hello, sir.

47
00:04:47,203 --> 00:04:49,872
My son is Paik Seung-yoo
and he'll be joining your course today.

48
00:04:49,956 --> 00:04:53,584
I see. But he has to pass
our placement test first.

49
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:56,796
Sir. Can anyone take a placement test now?

50
00:04:58,131 --> 00:04:59,882
I'm pulling Ye-lin out
of this cram school.

51
00:04:59,966 --> 00:05:02,719
How could the worst student
at Asung take a placement test here?

52
00:05:02,802 --> 00:05:04,095
Unbelievable.

53
00:05:05,221 --> 00:05:08,725
You're acting so haughty
because Ye-lin is the top student?

54
00:05:08,808 --> 00:05:10,643
She used to lag behind Seung-yoo
by a mile.

55
00:05:11,519 --> 00:05:13,938
What did you say? By a mile?

56
00:05:14,022 --> 00:05:16,649
It's a fact. You don't remember?
I can refresh your memory.

57
00:05:16,733 --> 00:05:20,153
-Go ahead and refresh my memory.
-Ye-lin scored 28 points back then…

58
00:05:20,236 --> 00:05:21,446
What? So what?

59
00:05:21,529 --> 00:05:24,657
Let me tell you again
because you can't remember!

60
00:05:30,413 --> 00:05:32,623
J&Y JUNG & YOON MATH ACADEMY
GLOBAL SIGMA LEARNING

61
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:44,302
2016 CSAT RECORD,
CLASS REGISTRATION FOR 2017 CSAT

62
00:06:14,916 --> 00:06:17,960
Oh, sir. I'm so sorry.

63
00:06:18,044 --> 00:06:20,129
I'll make sure he doesn't do that again.

64
00:06:20,213 --> 00:06:23,216
If you'll give my son
another chance, I'll bring…

65
00:06:23,299 --> 00:06:26,219
Hello? Sir? Hello?

66
00:06:29,639 --> 00:06:30,932
He didn't show up?

67
00:06:31,974 --> 00:06:33,017
No.

68
00:06:47,448 --> 00:06:49,283
POPULAR TEACHER JI YOON-SU
MENTORS GIFTED STUDENTS IN MATH

69
00:07:15,768 --> 00:07:18,229
-Please prepare a chateaubriand steak.
-Okay.

70
00:07:18,938 --> 00:07:21,232
It has a nice marbled look.

71
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:25,278
Where is my dad? Did he go somewhere?

72
00:07:28,030 --> 00:07:29,407
Did he go fishing again?

73
00:07:29,490 --> 00:07:31,367
He left very early…

74
00:07:32,243 --> 00:07:33,661
You were terrific today.

75
00:07:33,744 --> 00:07:36,998
I was on a roll, wasn't I?

76
00:07:37,081 --> 00:07:40,126
Oh, hey. Yeon-woo and I
went fishing together.

77
00:07:40,209 --> 00:07:41,544
Just a minute.

78
00:07:43,713 --> 00:07:47,300
Dad was amazing today.
He caught a huge fish.

79
00:07:49,135 --> 00:07:51,971
-Please cook spicy fish stew for dinner.
-Okay.

80
00:08:02,398 --> 00:08:03,774
All right.

81
00:08:04,984 --> 00:08:05,985
Cheers.

82
00:08:06,652 --> 00:08:11,032
It's too bad
you don't like spicy fish stew.

83
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:13,868
Jung-ah is a picky eater.

84
00:08:13,951 --> 00:08:14,952
I can make you sushi.

85
00:08:15,661 --> 00:08:17,288
No, thanks. Enjoy it.

86
00:08:18,706 --> 00:08:21,125
How is the high school
credit system faring?

87
00:08:21,709 --> 00:08:24,086
We're fully compliant. By the way--

88
00:08:24,170 --> 00:08:26,506
We're also going
to join the program, Father.

89
00:08:26,589 --> 00:08:27,423
I see.

90
00:08:27,507 --> 00:08:29,926
Grading the essay section
and written questions

91
00:08:30,009 --> 00:08:31,677
under the high school credit system
will be radically different.

92
00:08:31,761 --> 00:08:33,513
Oh, so then what?

93
00:08:33,596 --> 00:08:36,349
We're focusing
on the International Baccalaureate.

94
00:08:36,432 --> 00:08:40,603
Our International Middle School will focus
on debating skills and essay writing.

95
00:08:40,686 --> 00:08:45,316
Education needs to focus on producing
students who can become productive members

96
00:08:45,399 --> 00:08:47,610
of society and
be internationally competitive.

97
00:08:48,569 --> 00:08:51,531
I see. I'm excited about that.

98
00:08:51,614 --> 00:08:55,117
We're working on a special project
with the Ministry of Education.

99
00:08:56,536 --> 00:08:57,620
The Ministry of Education?

100
00:08:57,703 --> 00:09:00,122
We're planning to remake our school
into a school for the gifted.

101
00:09:00,206 --> 00:09:02,583
-Right.
-We have to pass the evaluations first,

102
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:05,127
so we think the special project
will boost our chances.

103
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:10,841
I don't know how you're planning it,
but you need to be careful.

104
00:09:13,386 --> 00:09:16,681
It'll look bad if the public learns about
any links between the ministry

105
00:09:16,764 --> 00:09:20,393
-and a private school.
-Yeon-woo has a good point.

106
00:09:20,476 --> 00:09:22,562
-You have to be careful.
-Sure.

107
00:09:23,229 --> 00:09:25,898
I was going to play golf
with Vice Minister Shin.

108
00:09:26,691 --> 00:09:29,694
But I think I'll have to delay it.

109
00:09:31,070 --> 00:09:32,113
All right.

110
00:09:33,364 --> 00:09:36,867
I'd like some sushi.

111
00:09:44,667 --> 00:09:47,128
It's finished. You can take it.

112
00:09:48,212 --> 00:09:49,255
Thanks.

113
00:09:49,338 --> 00:09:52,633
Oh, right.
I think I added too much wasabi.

114
00:09:53,384 --> 00:09:55,803
I know you don't like spicy foods.
Sorry about that.

115
00:09:55,886 --> 00:09:59,015
No need to be sorry. I won't eat it.

116
00:10:08,733 --> 00:10:09,692
What is it this time?

117
00:10:09,775 --> 00:10:13,446
Yeon-woo, can you raise the level
of the quality of your school?

118
00:10:13,529 --> 00:10:14,697
Quality?

119
00:10:14,780 --> 00:10:19,452
Parents around Hangok-dong are saying
that your school isn't good anymore.

120
00:10:19,535 --> 00:10:21,037
Did you know about that?

121
00:10:22,121 --> 00:10:24,582
-Fewer students got into top high schools.
-Jung-ah.

122
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:28,127
How long will you bend over
backward to please the parents?

123
00:10:29,629 --> 00:10:32,423
Are you a businessperson?
Try to be classy.

124
00:10:34,091 --> 00:10:36,093
You don't know anything about reality.

125
00:10:36,636 --> 00:10:39,013
The college admissions
isn't about education.

126
00:10:39,096 --> 00:10:40,473
It's spawned an industry.

127
00:10:40,556 --> 00:10:42,141
How could you say that?

128
00:10:42,224 --> 00:10:46,062
College admission results
bring prestige, power and fame.

129
00:10:47,647 --> 00:10:50,149
Analyze the needs of your clients
and produce results.

130
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:53,944
That's how you maintain our reputation
as a family of educators.

131
00:11:07,667 --> 00:11:11,420
You know, whenever
you talk about a "family of educators",

132
00:11:11,504 --> 00:11:12,588
it's laughable.

133
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:17,802
I mean, you didn't grow up with us.

134
00:11:20,262 --> 00:11:21,722
I like your strong work ethic though.

135
00:11:22,306 --> 00:11:25,810
My late grandfather,
Han Sung-pil, the school founder,

136
00:11:25,893 --> 00:11:27,603
would have been fond of you.

137
00:11:29,397 --> 00:11:33,651
He liked hardworking staff
who showed dedication.

138
00:11:36,779 --> 00:11:37,905
Oh, right.

139
00:11:38,572 --> 00:11:40,783
Asung High hired Ji Yoon-su
as a teacher, right?

140
00:11:42,284 --> 00:11:43,285
You know her?

141
00:11:43,369 --> 00:11:44,787
We went to Asung High together.

142
00:11:45,329 --> 00:11:47,998
But don't mention me to her.

143
00:12:07,268 --> 00:12:10,020
He's the fiance of Ji Yoon-su?

144
00:12:11,147 --> 00:12:13,732
He's an officer at the MoE,
and he oversees planning.

145
00:12:14,525 --> 00:12:15,776
Small world, right?

146
00:12:15,860 --> 00:12:18,737
It turns out he's the son
of former prime minister Ryu Hyun-il.

147
00:12:18,821 --> 00:12:21,949
No wonder Vice Minister Shin favors him.

148
00:12:22,908 --> 00:12:26,495
You'll add a high school category in
the International Mathematician Olympics?

149
00:12:26,579 --> 00:12:30,207
Yes, I think it'll spur interest
in science among high schoolers.

150
00:12:30,291 --> 00:12:32,793
And the Math Council
and the MoE will co-host it.

151
00:12:32,877 --> 00:12:34,086
It's a win-win.

152
00:12:34,170 --> 00:12:36,172
That'll raise the profile
of the Math Council

153
00:12:36,255 --> 00:12:39,300
and help the ministry get
good evaluation in the government report.

154
00:12:39,383 --> 00:12:40,885
Exactly.

155
00:12:40,968 --> 00:12:42,136
He's very smart.

156
00:12:42,219 --> 00:12:44,013
And he's good at execution.

157
00:12:44,096 --> 00:12:45,764
He's the opposite of Ji Yoon-su.

158
00:12:45,848 --> 00:12:46,724
How so?

159
00:12:48,976 --> 00:12:52,354
How will you select the judges?

160
00:12:52,938 --> 00:12:57,359
We'll have to appoint
a few of our people to the panel.

161
00:12:59,612 --> 00:13:00,905
But before we get to that,

162
00:13:01,947 --> 00:13:05,284
how will you choose
the team to represent Asung High?

163
00:13:05,367 --> 00:13:08,537
If they're chosen by the principal,
that'll create an uproar.

164
00:13:08,621 --> 00:13:12,082
We'll have to hold a school math contest
just for the sake of it.

165
00:13:12,166 --> 00:13:14,710
-All the students will compete in it.
-The entire school?

166
00:13:14,793 --> 00:13:16,545
We got so many complaints from parents

167
00:13:16,629 --> 00:13:19,590
when we sent a team drawn
from AP students to the English contest.

168
00:13:19,673 --> 00:13:22,885
So we can't pick a team like that anymore.

169
00:13:25,804 --> 00:13:29,767
But do you even like Ji Yoon-su?

170
00:13:29,850 --> 00:13:31,310
It doesn't seem like you do.

171
00:13:33,604 --> 00:13:37,316
I don't need her especially.

172
00:13:38,108 --> 00:13:39,568
Then what do you need?

173
00:13:40,402 --> 00:13:43,572
Just a vessel to guide
Asung High students.

174
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:49,787
All right.

175
00:13:54,166 --> 00:13:55,125
What's that?

176
00:13:55,209 --> 00:13:59,088
Just a second.
I need to submit this application today.

177
00:14:06,053 --> 00:14:08,138
-What?
-I have a surprise gift.

178
00:14:08,222 --> 00:14:09,807
A surprise gift?

179
00:14:11,559 --> 00:14:12,518
What is it?

180
00:14:12,601 --> 00:14:15,020
We're adding a high school category

181
00:14:15,854 --> 00:14:18,357
to the International
Mathematician Olympics.

182
00:14:19,191 --> 00:14:20,276
A high school category?

183
00:14:20,985 --> 00:14:24,446
And we'll co-host the Olympics
with the Math Council.

184
00:14:25,447 --> 00:14:27,157
That's fantastic.

185
00:14:28,450 --> 00:14:30,661
-Is it that great?
-Of course, it is.

186
00:14:31,412 --> 00:14:32,955
Then students from our school
can compete too, right?

187
00:14:33,038 --> 00:14:35,207
Asung High will probably send one student.

188
00:14:37,042 --> 00:14:39,295
How's work? You started teaching classes.

189
00:14:40,212 --> 00:14:41,255
Oh, right.

190
00:14:42,047 --> 00:14:44,884
Did you meet the director?
She's the chairman's daughter.

191
00:14:45,467 --> 00:14:46,302
Yes.

192
00:14:47,511 --> 00:14:49,305
She's peculiar.

193
00:14:49,388 --> 00:14:51,849
Their family makes all the decisions,

194
00:14:51,932 --> 00:14:54,935
so they have got more power
than the principal or vice-principal.

195
00:14:55,769 --> 00:14:58,564
Even though the director
was born out of wedlock,

196
00:14:58,647 --> 00:15:01,275
rumor has it that
she's in contention to succeed her dad.

197
00:15:01,984 --> 00:15:05,321
They say she has complete control
over the foundation operations.

198
00:15:06,906 --> 00:15:07,907
Are you listening?

199
00:15:07,990 --> 00:15:11,577
So when will they
announce the Competition?

200
00:15:11,660 --> 00:15:14,288
I'm talking about
more important stuff than that.

201
00:15:14,371 --> 00:15:16,749
-He'd be a great contestant.
-Who?

202
00:15:17,541 --> 00:15:18,751
I told you before.

203
00:15:19,335 --> 00:15:21,587
There is a Ramanujan in our school.

204
00:15:55,621 --> 00:15:56,705
Paik Seung-yoo?

205
00:15:57,373 --> 00:16:00,709
Yes. Can I see his student record
from last semester?

206
00:16:00,793 --> 00:16:02,795
Oh, sure.

207
00:16:04,129 --> 00:16:06,882
But why? Did he get into any trouble?

208
00:16:07,466 --> 00:16:09,134
No, it's nothing like that.

209
00:16:09,802 --> 00:16:11,845
I'm just curious about him.

210
00:16:12,471 --> 00:16:15,391
STUDENT RECORD: PAIK SEUNG-YOO

211
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:21,063
10TH GRADE, MATH, 9TH PERCENTILE

212
00:16:23,148 --> 00:16:26,986
11TH GRADE, MATH, 9TH PERCENTILE

213
00:16:34,535 --> 00:16:36,120
A school math contest?

214
00:16:36,996 --> 00:16:40,207
The Ministry of Education is
co-hosting the Mathematician Olympics

215
00:16:40,290 --> 00:16:42,292
and they will add a high school category.

216
00:16:43,544 --> 00:16:45,504
YOUTH MATHEMATICS SPEECH COMPETITION

217
00:16:45,587 --> 00:16:47,131
Oh, right.

218
00:16:48,298 --> 00:16:50,092
Did your boyfriend tell you?

219
00:16:52,136 --> 00:16:53,595
How do you know him?

220
00:16:54,847 --> 00:16:56,140
He works at the MoE, right?

221
00:16:59,768 --> 00:17:02,479
It says each school
can only send one contestant.

222
00:17:03,522 --> 00:17:04,606
Yes.

223
00:17:04,690 --> 00:17:07,693
So we'll pick the student
who wins the school math contest?

224
00:17:08,569 --> 00:17:10,654
Please collaborate
with the other math teachers

225
00:17:10,738 --> 00:17:12,948
to come up with problems that
can accurately assess math skills.

226
00:17:13,032 --> 00:17:14,908
All right. I'll get right to it.

227
00:17:19,955 --> 00:17:24,668
Oh, I found the student
who solved the problem.

228
00:17:25,252 --> 00:17:27,212
Oh really? Who was it?

229
00:17:28,130 --> 00:17:29,214
I won't tell you.

230
00:17:31,133 --> 00:17:32,634
But you'll figure it out anyway.

231
00:17:32,718 --> 00:17:35,596
Because that student is very gifted.

232
00:17:44,313 --> 00:17:45,481
IMO 2017
YOUTH MATHEMATICS SPEECH COMPETITION

233
00:17:45,564 --> 00:17:46,982
I presume you all know.

234
00:17:47,566 --> 00:17:49,401
The International Mathematician Olympics

235
00:17:49,485 --> 00:17:52,571
that mathematicians around the world
look forward to every year.

236
00:17:53,447 --> 00:17:55,407
Our country will host it
for the first time.

237
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:59,828
What's amazing is that
you'll have a chance to compete in it.

238
00:18:02,122 --> 00:18:03,040
But how?

239
00:18:03,123 --> 00:18:06,251
There will be a high school category
in the Olympics.

240
00:18:06,335 --> 00:18:09,797
We'll hold a math contest to pick
one student to represent the school.

241
00:18:13,092 --> 00:18:16,804
I'll also choose the math club team
based on the math contest results.

242
00:18:16,887 --> 00:18:19,681
So enter the contest
if you want to join the math club.

243
00:18:19,765 --> 00:18:20,891
-Okay.
-Okay.

244
00:18:23,102 --> 00:18:26,146
Memorize all of this
for our next class. Got it?

245
00:18:26,230 --> 00:18:27,272
-Okay.
-Class is over.

246
00:18:27,773 --> 00:18:29,566
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

247
00:18:32,444 --> 00:18:34,071
Take a nap after I leave, slacker!

248
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:37,449
-Goodbye, Teacher.
-Goodbye, Teacher.

249
00:18:42,079 --> 00:18:43,247
Hey, Paik Seung-yoo.

250
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:47,292
What a nice camera.

251
00:18:48,710 --> 00:18:50,963
Hey, don't touch it. It's not yours.

252
00:18:51,547 --> 00:18:53,757
Ms. Ji Yoon-su wants
to see you in her classroom.

253
00:18:53,841 --> 00:18:55,467
Bring that with you.

254
00:19:22,452 --> 00:19:24,663
You're here. Come in.

255
00:19:34,089 --> 00:19:36,466
-Connect your camera to the laptop.
-For what?

256
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:39,678
I was thinking about using your photos
to make a course material.

257
00:19:40,429 --> 00:19:42,848
But maybe we can do something
more interesting.

258
00:19:56,778 --> 00:19:57,946
Wait a minute.

259
00:20:02,701 --> 00:20:05,704
-Let's put the photos in here.
-What photos?

260
00:20:05,787 --> 00:20:08,957
Cycloid, Fractal, and Tessellation.

261
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:10,042
CYCLOID: LOCUS OF A POINT
ON THE RIM OF A CIRCLE OF RADIUS

262
00:20:10,125 --> 00:20:11,126
FRACTAL: INFINITELY COMPLEX PATTERNS,
SELF-SIMILAR ACROSS DIFFERENT SCALES

263
00:20:11,210 --> 00:20:12,377
I saw your photos.

264
00:20:12,461 --> 00:20:13,795
TESSELLATION: TILING OF A PLANE
USING ONE OR MORE GEOMETRIC SHAPES

265
00:20:17,549 --> 00:20:19,426
All right. Next, type this.

266
00:20:21,803 --> 00:20:25,474
These are not photos of an eave, branch,

267
00:20:26,266 --> 00:20:28,185
or window.

268
00:20:33,065 --> 00:20:35,275
Type that down. Below the photo.

269
00:20:42,908 --> 00:20:46,662
If you look at it through the lens
of math, you'll see something new.

270
00:20:52,584 --> 00:20:53,627
Hold on.

271
00:21:01,969 --> 00:21:03,053
Okay.

272
00:21:04,721 --> 00:21:07,057
Now type below the photos.

273
00:21:10,352 --> 00:21:11,478
Quote.

274
00:21:12,020 --> 00:21:16,066
Taking applications
to select a contestant…

275
00:21:23,615 --> 00:21:27,536
who will represent Asung High at the 2017
International Mathematician Olympics.

276
00:21:28,829 --> 00:21:31,540
Date and time: 10:00 a.m.,

277
00:21:32,541 --> 00:21:35,210
September 9, 2017.

278
00:21:35,836 --> 00:21:39,047
Venue: Asung High auditorium.

279
00:21:39,131 --> 00:21:40,132
No quota limits.

280
00:21:41,133 --> 00:21:43,885
Anyone can enter.

281
00:21:44,511 --> 00:21:45,971
Unquote.

282
00:21:48,849 --> 00:21:50,058
Let's take a look.

283
00:21:54,187 --> 00:21:55,439
Will you enter?

284
00:21:57,149 --> 00:21:58,317
No.

285
00:22:02,529 --> 00:22:03,488
That's done.

286
00:22:05,907 --> 00:22:06,950
Can I go?

287
00:22:09,661 --> 00:22:11,830
I wonder why you didn't come
in the morning

288
00:22:11,913 --> 00:22:13,957
and why you're
in the 9th percentile in math.

289
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:18,503
You say you don't like math,
but you obviously like it.

290
00:22:19,921 --> 00:22:22,174
I've got questions,
but I won't ask you anything.

291
00:22:22,257 --> 00:22:23,091
But instead…

292
00:22:33,351 --> 00:22:36,354
WHAT'S THE PROBABILITY

293
00:22:36,438 --> 00:22:40,942
WHEN "N" POINTS ARE RANDOMLY SELECTED
INSIDE A CIRCLE,

294
00:22:41,026 --> 00:22:43,320
THEY FORM VERTICES
OF A CONVEX N-GON? (WITH N≥4)

295
00:22:46,031 --> 00:22:48,033
Try to solve this problem.

296
00:22:50,118 --> 00:22:51,995
Come here tomorrow at 7:30 a.m.

297
00:22:53,497 --> 00:22:54,331
Why should I?

298
00:22:55,457 --> 00:22:58,335
When mathematicians work on a proof,
they become candid.

299
00:22:59,711 --> 00:23:01,463
I want to see that side of you.

300
00:23:01,546 --> 00:23:04,549
So why do I need to be candid with you?

301
00:23:06,384 --> 00:23:11,014
-Think I can help your career in some way?
-Do you think you're special?

302
00:23:14,142 --> 00:23:15,644
Do you think you're a genius?

303
00:23:18,438 --> 00:23:20,649
There are a lot of students
who have a gift like yours.

304
00:23:20,732 --> 00:23:21,983
And do you also know this?

305
00:23:22,567 --> 00:23:25,529
Among famous mathematicians,
a few of them have a low IQ.

306
00:23:25,612 --> 00:23:28,240
So why are you asking me to do this?

307
00:23:31,785 --> 00:23:33,954
It's not because you have a special gift.

308
00:23:37,666 --> 00:23:41,711
But you have a perspective on math,
and that is quite unique.

309
00:23:46,925 --> 00:23:47,926
I like it.

310
00:23:50,637 --> 00:23:51,847
Don't be late tomorrow.

311
00:24:05,443 --> 00:24:07,112
WHAT'S THE PROBABILITY WHEN "N" POINTS
