312
00:24:07,195 --> 00:24:08,947
INSIDE A CIRCLE, THEY FORM VERTICES
OF A CONVEX N-GON? (WITH N≥4)

313
00:24:16,163 --> 00:24:17,289
Excuse me.

314
00:24:18,165 --> 00:24:19,958
You must be Ms. Ji Yoon-su, right?

315
00:24:20,041 --> 00:24:21,626
Yes, that's me.

316
00:24:21,710 --> 00:24:25,380
I'm Paik Seung-yoo's dad.
He's a junior here.

317
00:24:26,631 --> 00:24:28,258
You're his father?

318
00:24:40,687 --> 00:24:42,606
So your son…

319
00:24:42,689 --> 00:24:43,940
Do you remember the news back then?

320
00:24:44,024 --> 00:24:47,152
A math genius
who enrolled in MIT at age 10.

321
00:24:47,235 --> 00:24:49,696
But that boy's name was Paik Min-jae.

322
00:24:49,779 --> 00:24:51,156
He changed his name.

323
00:24:52,657 --> 00:24:56,703
When he returned from America,
he was labeled as a failure.

324
00:25:03,210 --> 00:25:04,544
What do you think?

325
00:25:07,172 --> 00:25:09,174
-He's quite different.
-What?

326
00:25:11,259 --> 00:25:13,929
You mean right now?

327
00:25:14,804 --> 00:25:16,890
He's going through puberty.

328
00:25:17,974 --> 00:25:19,017
Puberty?

329
00:25:19,100 --> 00:25:21,186
Teenagers go through a rebellious period.

330
00:25:21,269 --> 00:25:23,230
He's in the throes of teenage angst.

331
00:25:26,483 --> 00:25:29,527
But why did you come to see me?

332
00:25:29,611 --> 00:25:32,697
I heard that you teach
gifted students very well.

333
00:25:33,323 --> 00:25:35,700
I don't think you've met a boy
like Seung-yoo though.

334
00:25:36,368 --> 00:25:38,787
You'll find him a delight to teach.

335
00:25:38,870 --> 00:25:42,249
Could you also prepare him to compete
in the Math Olympiad?

336
00:25:42,332 --> 00:25:44,209
Please guide him to a better future.

337
00:25:45,669 --> 00:25:50,257
I don't know anything
about his past though.

338
00:25:50,340 --> 00:25:52,592
Well, if you spend time with him…

339
00:25:52,676 --> 00:25:54,886
Do you know what happened
to him in America?

340
00:25:57,305 --> 00:25:59,266
Regardless of what happened,

341
00:25:59,975 --> 00:26:02,185
it's already been eight years
since he came back.

342
00:26:02,269 --> 00:26:03,603
Eight years?

343
00:26:08,108 --> 00:26:12,654
But the talent he has
doesn't just vanish, you know.

344
00:26:13,405 --> 00:26:15,323
If you could guide him…

345
00:26:15,407 --> 00:26:18,994
I don't think Seung-yoo needs
my guidance right now.

346
00:26:19,995 --> 00:26:22,163
Then what do you think he needs?

347
00:26:22,789 --> 00:26:26,209
I don't know what that is yet.

348
00:26:27,335 --> 00:26:29,546
I'm sorry that I can't be of any help.

349
00:26:32,048 --> 00:26:32,966
Well…

350
00:26:37,512 --> 00:26:38,888
What do you mean?

351
00:26:38,972 --> 00:26:43,268
I don't think it's necessary
to let all the students compete

352
00:26:43,351 --> 00:26:44,602
in the school math contest.

353
00:26:47,063 --> 00:26:47,897
Why?

354
00:26:49,691 --> 00:26:51,443
Because it's unnecessary competition.

355
00:26:52,110 --> 00:26:53,445
Unnecessary competition…

356
00:26:53,528 --> 00:26:57,407
It serves no purpose to have poor students
enter the math contest.

357
00:26:57,490 --> 00:27:00,702
Is there a criterion where specific
students shouldn't enter a contest?

358
00:27:01,953 --> 00:27:04,247
And another criterion
for students who can enter?

359
00:27:08,376 --> 00:27:09,627
Who will decide that?

360
00:27:10,337 --> 00:27:12,255
Me? You?

361
00:27:13,340 --> 00:27:14,549
Or your dad?

362
00:27:20,347 --> 00:27:22,932
I'm sorry for being thoughtless.

363
00:27:30,065 --> 00:27:31,274
Ye-lin.

364
00:27:36,780 --> 00:27:40,617
I see that
you're feeling a lot of pressure.

365
00:27:43,787 --> 00:27:45,622
The school and your parents

366
00:27:47,040 --> 00:27:50,627
expect a lot from you, don't they?

367
00:27:57,467 --> 00:27:59,135
Ye-lin.

368
00:28:00,637 --> 00:28:02,889
But you still have to try your best.

369
00:28:06,142 --> 00:28:07,310
Otherwise,

370
00:28:08,686 --> 00:28:09,938
I'll drop you.

371
00:28:13,858 --> 00:28:18,154
You know there are other gifted students
besides you here, right?

372
00:28:21,366 --> 00:28:22,367
Answer me.

373
00:28:23,618 --> 00:28:24,828
Yes, ma'am.

374
00:28:27,497 --> 00:28:29,040
All right. You're dismissed.

