00:45:23,971 --> 00:45:25,389
the right commission members?

508
00:45:28,100 --> 00:45:31,103
If you secure a school
for the gifted in your district,

509
00:45:31,854 --> 00:45:35,899
won't it help you get re-elected?

510
00:45:48,662 --> 00:45:50,539
I'll do everything possible.

511
00:45:51,665 --> 00:45:54,293
In return, you'll handle
that math contest matter, right?

512
00:45:54,376 --> 00:45:58,755
In addition to that,
Ye-lin's academic standings can't fall.

513
00:46:09,558 --> 00:46:13,896
VICE-PRINCIPAL CHOI SUNG-HAN

514
00:46:20,861 --> 00:46:23,655
MATH GENIUS PAIK MIN-JAE,
LEARNING MATHEMATICS AT COLLEGE

515
00:46:39,588 --> 00:46:41,089
YOUR LOAN INTEREST PAYMENT
IS DUE ON THE 20TH

516
00:46:41,173 --> 00:46:42,007
ASUNG HIGH SCHOOL

517
00:46:42,090 --> 00:46:43,175
Asung High?

518
00:46:45,135 --> 00:46:48,555
-Oh, hello?
-Am I talking to Paik Seung-yoo's father?

519
00:46:48,639 --> 00:46:50,390
Yes, this is he.

520
00:46:50,474 --> 00:46:53,143
Hello, I'm Choi Sung-han,
Vice-principal at Asung High.

521
00:46:53,227 --> 00:46:56,563
Hello, sir. Why are you calling?

522
00:46:56,647 --> 00:46:59,107
Could you meet me tomorrow at school?

523
00:46:59,191 --> 00:47:00,234
Pardon?

524
00:47:01,401 --> 00:47:02,361
Sure.

525
00:47:03,028 --> 00:47:05,739
What is this about, may I ask?

526
00:47:05,822 --> 00:47:07,741
I'll tell you everything tomorrow.

527
00:47:08,367 --> 00:47:09,785
I'll see you tomorrow then.

528
00:47:09,868 --> 00:47:11,787
Okay, Sir. Good night.

529
00:47:15,374 --> 00:47:17,167
What kind of trouble did he get into?

530
00:47:34,685 --> 00:47:36,270
NATURAL SCIENCE

531
00:48:03,380 --> 00:48:08,302
A MATHEMATICIAN'S APOLOGY
BY G.H.HARDY

532
00:48:15,475 --> 00:48:17,352
THE MUSIC OF THE PRIMES
THE RIEMANN HYPOTHESIS

533
00:48:50,636 --> 00:48:54,723
1729, IT IS A VERY INTERESTING NUMBER,
THE SMALLEST NUMBER EXPRESSIBLE

534
00:48:54,806 --> 00:48:58,769
AS THE SUM OF TWO CUBES
IN TWO DIFFERENT WAYS

535
00:49:03,940 --> 00:49:06,318
A MATHEMATICIAN'S APOLOGY
BY G.H.HARDY

536
00:49:40,185 --> 00:49:42,270
-It's all done.
-Thank you.

537
00:51:23,288 --> 00:51:24,873
Congratulations.

538
00:51:27,209 --> 00:51:28,251
I…

539
00:51:29,544 --> 00:51:30,754
Seung-yoo is…

540
00:51:31,338 --> 00:51:34,216
Yes, I think he's regained his focus.

541
00:51:36,218 --> 00:51:39,721
You need to be very supportive now.

542
00:51:42,516 --> 00:51:43,475
You can't

543
00:51:44,142 --> 00:51:46,520
let him fail twice.

544
00:51:46,603 --> 00:51:49,481
Of course, not.

545
00:51:49,564 --> 00:51:53,318
As the director of school affairs,
our school values a gifted student

546
00:51:53,401 --> 00:51:54,986
like Seung-yoo,

547
00:51:55,695 --> 00:51:58,406
but what's important is his future,

548
00:51:59,074 --> 00:52:00,742
not something for the school.

549
00:52:02,452 --> 00:52:03,453
Yes.

550
00:52:05,330 --> 00:52:08,375
Finding the equation

551
00:52:08,458 --> 00:52:11,253
of a parabola…

552
00:52:11,962 --> 00:52:16,550
-Gosh. You like math, Min-jae?
-Yes.

553
00:52:16,633 --> 00:52:18,385
How much do you like it?

554
00:52:18,468 --> 00:52:20,262
One hundred percent!

555
00:52:20,846 --> 00:52:24,641
-One hundred percent?
-Min-jae, have some fried chicken.

556
00:52:25,600 --> 00:52:29,187
Wow. You like math
more than you like fried chicken.

557
00:52:29,271 --> 00:52:30,188
Yes.

558
00:52:31,731 --> 00:52:35,360
-Are you not going to eat?
-No matter what people say about our son

559
00:52:35,443 --> 00:52:36,945
that he turned into a dummy,

560
00:52:38,697 --> 00:52:42,033
Seung-yoo still has the skills,
doesn't he?

561
00:52:43,368 --> 00:52:44,494
Yes.

562
00:52:45,954 --> 00:52:49,082
He never lost it. Min-jae.

563
00:52:49,165 --> 00:52:50,584
Min-jae.

564
00:53:11,021 --> 00:53:11,938
Ms. Ji.

565
00:53:13,231 --> 00:53:14,816
What? Seung-yoo.

566
00:53:16,651 --> 00:53:19,279
-You live here too?
-Yes.

567
00:53:19,362 --> 00:53:21,698
-He's a student?
-Yes. He goes to our school.

568
00:53:21,781 --> 00:53:23,408
Could you return my umbrella?

569
00:53:24,409 --> 00:53:27,078
-Your umbrella?
-I let you borrow it. Last time.

570
00:53:28,455 --> 00:53:29,623
I remember.

571
00:53:30,498 --> 00:53:33,627
-You need it now?
-Yes, right now. I need it.

572
00:53:36,254 --> 00:53:38,173
Sure.

573
00:53:38,798 --> 00:53:40,634
Wait a minute. I'll bring it down.

574
00:54:01,571 --> 00:54:03,782
Seung-yoo. Where are you?

575
00:54:04,366 --> 00:54:05,408
I'm almost home.

576
00:54:05,492 --> 00:54:07,744
You are? Then get here quickly.

577
00:54:08,411 --> 00:54:09,537
Okay.

578
00:54:12,457 --> 00:54:15,460
So you're the person whose bag
got mixed up with hers on the train?

579
00:54:15,543 --> 00:54:17,504
And you also go to Asung High?

580
00:54:17,587 --> 00:54:19,798
What a coincidence.

581
00:54:20,882 --> 00:54:23,677
I hope you'll get along with…

582
00:54:30,850 --> 00:54:31,977
What?

583
00:54:35,480 --> 00:54:36,856
I'm home.

584
00:54:37,899 --> 00:54:39,484
Seung-yoo!

585
00:54:40,068 --> 00:54:41,695
Oh, my son.

586
00:54:44,239 --> 00:54:47,325
I'm so proud of you.

587
00:54:48,535 --> 00:54:49,703
Get ready.

588
00:54:51,037 --> 00:54:53,164
Transfer to a science high school.

589
00:54:53,915 --> 00:54:54,958
Let's start over.

590
00:54:57,127 --> 00:54:58,628
Your teacher told me everything.

591
00:54:59,462 --> 00:55:01,589
You can do well
if you put your mind to it.

592
00:55:01,673 --> 00:55:03,508
Why did you make us worry so much?

593
00:55:06,261 --> 00:55:09,264
I received a letter of recommendation
from your school.

594
00:55:09,973 --> 00:55:12,809
I'll hire a tutor,
so prepare for the admission exam.

595
00:55:15,562 --> 00:55:16,688
I'm not going.

596
00:55:18,314 --> 00:55:20,108
-Seung-yoo.
-I'm not doing it.

597
00:55:20,775 --> 00:55:21,901
I'm not going there!

598
00:55:21,985 --> 00:55:23,570
-Come on, Seung-yoo.
-You won't go?

599
00:55:23,653 --> 00:55:25,030
Why you!

600
00:55:25,113 --> 00:55:28,408
Wait. Honey, please!

601
00:55:28,491 --> 00:55:29,826
Look at those trophies!

602
00:55:29,909 --> 00:55:30,910
Look at it!

603
00:55:32,996 --> 00:55:35,081
I've been patient
with you for eight years.

604
00:55:36,499 --> 00:55:39,169
Sometimes, I told myself
you were dead to me.

605
00:55:39,252 --> 00:55:41,671
That made me feel better for a while.

606
00:55:42,255 --> 00:55:43,673
Fill this with trophies again!

607
00:55:44,299 --> 00:55:47,844
Until you do as I say,
you can't do whatever you want.

608
00:55:48,803 --> 00:55:50,472
Fill this with trophies again!

609
00:55:51,181 --> 00:55:52,474
Answer me!

610
00:55:53,224 --> 00:55:54,893
I said answer me!

611
00:56:16,164 --> 00:56:17,290
What is this?

612
00:56:18,124 --> 00:56:20,293
I'm taking those to school.

613
00:56:21,211 --> 00:56:22,712
A MATHEMATICIAN'S APOLOGY
BY G.H.HARDY

614
00:56:22,796 --> 00:56:24,672
These are your dad's books, aren't they?

615
00:56:25,340 --> 00:56:26,424
Yes, that's right.

616
00:56:27,133 --> 00:56:29,385
Why take them to school?
Just throw them out.

617
00:56:33,431 --> 00:56:36,976
I know. You can donate them
to your school library.

618
00:56:37,060 --> 00:56:39,020
They're hard-to-find books, right?

619
00:56:45,985 --> 00:56:48,029
Next week, when will we look at dresses?

620
00:56:48,113 --> 00:56:49,823
-Thursday.
-Right.

621
00:56:50,532 --> 00:56:52,242
I'll get going. Go inside.

622
00:57:06,756 --> 00:57:07,590
Seung-yoo.

623
00:57:18,935 --> 00:57:20,478
What's the matter?

624
00:57:23,898 --> 00:57:25,358
Science high school?

625
00:57:26,568 --> 00:57:28,403
What? What are you talking about?

626
00:57:29,487 --> 00:57:33,533
You're Paik Seung-yoo
and not Paik Min-jae anymore.

627
00:57:34,784 --> 00:57:36,453
I'm glad to meet you.

628
00:57:39,122 --> 00:57:40,540
You lied to me.

629
00:58:18,244 --> 00:58:19,829
Seung-yoo's dad called?

630
00:58:19,913 --> 00:58:22,165
Yes, he called earlier.

631
00:58:22,248 --> 00:58:25,210
Seung-yoo has a school interview today
and has to leave early.

632
00:58:26,586 --> 00:58:30,673
I heard that Seung-yoo
was a famous math genius years ago.

633
00:58:33,259 --> 00:58:35,303
Is that why you took an interest in him?

634
00:58:42,644 --> 00:58:43,811
Paik Seung-yoo!

635
00:58:44,312 --> 00:58:46,564
Ms. Ji Yoon-su wants you
to come to her classroom.

636
00:59:12,799 --> 00:59:14,092
Sit down.

637
00:59:18,930 --> 00:59:20,473
Let's do this together.

638
00:59:22,350 --> 00:59:23,560
Let's do math together.

639
00:59:25,895 --> 00:59:27,522
Don't go to that school. Learn math here.

640
00:59:27,605 --> 00:59:29,774
You told my dad
I should go to a science school.

641
00:59:31,442 --> 00:59:33,570
I don't know how things led to that.

642
00:59:34,445 --> 00:59:35,989
But I'll talk to your dad.

643
00:59:39,784 --> 00:59:42,787
It doesn't matter
if you're a math genius or not.

644
00:59:43,454 --> 00:59:46,165
It doesn't matter if you can
still do math like you used to.

645
00:59:46,874 --> 00:59:47,709
But…

646
00:59:50,211 --> 00:59:52,422
You know how it feels and so do I.

647
00:59:55,800 --> 00:59:59,554
When you're solving a problem,
you don't hear anything else.

648
00:59:59,637 --> 01:00:01,556
There's nothingness in that moment.

649
01:00:18,239 --> 01:00:20,241
You feel totally free.

650
01:00:23,202 --> 01:00:26,456
Don't give up on that, Seung-yoo.

651
01:00:39,218 --> 01:00:40,261
Hello?

652
01:00:43,681 --> 01:00:44,766
Right now?

653
01:00:48,227 --> 01:00:49,228
Okay.

654
01:00:55,485 --> 01:00:57,362
-I have to go now.
-Seung-yoo.

655
01:00:59,530 --> 01:01:03,159
I couldn't solve that problem.

656
01:01:05,953 --> 01:01:07,580
I thought I could.

657
01:01:09,207 --> 01:01:11,751
But I couldn't solve it.
I'm going to give up.

658
01:01:14,212 --> 01:01:16,214
You said there are unsolvable problems.

659
01:02:04,262 --> 01:02:05,346
Get in. Hurry.

660
01:02:06,806 --> 01:02:08,015
Wait!

661
01:02:12,854 --> 01:02:15,857
Mr. Paik, let me teach Seung-yoo.

662
01:02:17,442 --> 01:02:19,360
You told me you couldn't help him.

663
01:02:19,986 --> 01:02:22,447
You changed your mind
since I'm transferring him?

664
01:02:24,157 --> 01:02:26,659
I'm sorry but it's too late, Ms. Ji.

665
01:02:27,452 --> 01:02:29,620
-Now get in, son.
-You have to leave him alone.

666
01:02:29,704 --> 01:02:30,747
What?

667
01:02:30,830 --> 01:02:33,875
Seung-yoo can reach his abilities
only if you stop constraining him.

668
01:02:39,297 --> 01:02:42,049
Learn math from me, okay?

669
01:02:46,262 --> 01:02:47,430
I can't believe this.

670
01:02:48,264 --> 01:02:50,349
Now, get out of the way.

671
01:02:50,433 --> 01:02:51,392
Get in the car.

672
01:02:52,101 --> 01:02:53,102
Get in.

673
01:03:00,818 --> 01:03:02,403
Have a good day, Ms. Ji.

674
01:03:40,566 --> 01:03:43,236
What a teacher. Unbelievable.

675
01:03:44,070 --> 01:03:46,322
She refused to teach you when I asked her.

676
01:03:47,365 --> 01:03:49,450
-When did you meet her?
-Who?

677
01:03:50,451 --> 01:03:51,577
Ms. Ji?

678
01:03:52,912 --> 01:03:54,080
On Monday.

679
01:03:56,624 --> 01:03:58,543
I felt like I was imposing it on you.

680
01:03:58,626 --> 01:04:02,255
I'd like you to be free
from any constraints.

681
01:04:05,800 --> 01:04:10,346
Thanks to your school director's
recommendation,

682
01:04:11,514 --> 01:04:14,892
the science school called.
They want you to come in for an interview.

683
01:04:15,601 --> 01:04:17,854
-Then we're…
-I've waited for this day.

684
01:04:19,105 --> 01:04:21,399
I prayed so hard.

685
01:04:24,110 --> 01:04:25,278
Win the Nobel Prize, son.

686
01:04:25,361 --> 01:04:27,280
There is no Nobel Prize for math.

687
01:04:27,363 --> 01:04:30,157
The other medal they give…
The ones equivalent to a Nobel.

688
01:04:31,325 --> 01:04:33,494
Or work at NASA on rockets.

689
01:04:34,453 --> 01:04:38,791
Be a professor at Cambridge or MIT.

690
01:04:38,875 --> 01:04:41,878
Set up a math institute
with your name on it.

691
01:04:44,672 --> 01:04:48,050
Don't be like your old man.
Do great things.

692
01:05:06,110 --> 01:05:08,070
Can I do those things at Asung High?

693
01:05:08,154 --> 01:05:11,741
-What can Asung High offer?
-Mathematics. I'll try hard.

694
01:05:11,824 --> 01:05:15,328
We put the apartment up for sale.
I'm going to sell the cafe too.

695
01:05:16,037 --> 01:05:19,498
You can stay at the school dorm.
They have one there.

696
01:05:20,207 --> 01:05:24,170
We're going to pay off all our debts
and move to a small town.

697
01:05:24,962 --> 01:05:26,255
It's decided.

698
01:05:29,383 --> 01:05:30,468
MATH CLASSROOM

699
01:05:32,303 --> 01:05:34,096
Isn't the second problem too difficult?

700
01:05:34,180 --> 01:05:35,932
Who cares? It's a math contest.

701
01:05:36,015 --> 01:05:39,226
There are too many complex equations
you have to use to solve it.

702
01:05:39,310 --> 01:05:41,270
Should we make that the last problem?

703
01:05:41,354 --> 01:05:44,023
Or we could reduce the number of problems.

704
01:05:44,649 --> 01:05:47,985
It's okay. The students will choose
which ones they'll solve.

705
01:05:48,861 --> 01:05:51,864
It'll be so hard to grade them.

706
01:05:51,948 --> 01:05:55,034
We have to determine the point system too.

707
01:06:07,964 --> 01:06:10,800
YOU ARE IN CONTROL OF YOUR DESTINY

708
01:06:14,303 --> 01:06:18,349
NOBEL WINNER IN CHEMISTRY,
NOBEL WINNER IN PHYSIOLOGY OR MEDICINE

709
01:06:30,778 --> 01:06:32,363
Let's go for lunch.

710
01:06:32,446 --> 01:06:34,699
-I'm famished.
-Good job.

711
01:06:34,782 --> 01:06:36,492
Wait for me.

712
01:06:36,575 --> 01:06:38,035
What are you going to have?

713
01:06:57,304 --> 01:06:59,056
MATH CLASSROOM

714
01:07:06,605 --> 01:07:09,525
ASUNG HIGH SCHOOL MATH CONTEST

715
01:07:20,995 --> 01:07:24,081
You think you can do well
on the admission exam?

716
01:07:26,250 --> 01:07:28,669
Don't get nervous.
Call me after you're done.

717
01:07:30,046 --> 01:07:31,088
Okay.

718
01:07:57,323 --> 01:07:58,783
Ye-lin.

719
01:07:58,866 --> 01:08:00,910
I took care of it.

720
01:08:00,993 --> 01:08:03,329
So now you just have to
perform well, okay?

721
01:08:03,412 --> 01:08:04,538
Okay.

722
01:09:17,486 --> 01:09:19,613
2017 SCIENCE HIGH SCHOOL ADMISSIONS EXAM

723
01:09:32,293 --> 01:09:37,965
PROVE THAT THERE IS
ONLY ONE PLANE THAT INCLUDES POINT P

724
01:10:03,657 --> 01:10:06,035
ASUNG HIGH SCHOOL MATH CONTEST

725
01:10:09,038 --> 01:10:11,248
We don't know who among you

726
01:10:11,332 --> 01:10:13,959
will compete in the International
Mathematician Olympics.

727
01:10:15,628 --> 01:10:19,882
It's a rare opportunity,
so pour all your energy into it.

728
01:10:22,676 --> 01:10:25,804
I hope you'll do your best,
Asung High students. Shall we begin?

729
01:10:28,390 --> 01:10:29,308
There's…

730
01:10:32,353 --> 01:10:33,979
still some time left.

731
01:10:38,025 --> 01:10:40,444
All right. We have to follow the schedule.

732
01:10:40,527 --> 01:10:43,030
How about we pass out
the blank answer sheets first?

733
01:10:44,114 --> 01:10:45,282
Let's begin.

734
01:10:50,537 --> 01:10:52,206
Pass out the blank sheets.

735
01:11:06,136 --> 01:11:09,181
Shall we close the door now?

736
01:11:55,894 --> 01:11:57,146
I solved it.

737
01:11:59,398 --> 01:12:02,651
I solved the problem.

738
01:12:44,777 --> 01:12:47,446
Don't worry about Paik Seung-yoo.
He's not the competition.

739
01:12:47,529 --> 01:12:49,198
Try to take care of it.

740
01:12:49,281 --> 01:12:53,118
I wonder how this will grow
under your stubborn personality.

741
01:12:53,202 --> 01:12:54,953
Are you sure you won't regret it?

742
01:12:55,037 --> 01:12:56,747
You should be worried.

743
01:12:56,830 --> 01:12:59,083
You might never
get the top score in math again.

744
01:12:59,166 --> 01:13:01,627
I'll explain everything later.
It's really important.

745
01:13:01,710 --> 01:13:03,712
More important than
our wedding preparations?

746
01:13:03,796 --> 01:13:06,757
-Why are you suddenly acting like this?
-It's not sudden.

747
01:13:06,840 --> 01:13:08,550
I want to learn more about you.
Don't hide who you are.

748
01:13:08,634 --> 01:13:11,595
Really? Can I really show you
everything about me?

749
01:13:12,137 --> 01:13:17,142
